reviews.text: One of the best place to relax, meditate and contemplate on just yourself.  The ambience is amazing and the artistic features of the Cathedral are just mind blowing.
Cathedral in the heart of Galway city, built on former gaol grounds. Established in late 1950s, with stunning architecture and murals. Free entry - donations accepted.

What a beautiful cathedral that was built 50+ years ago but looks and feels like it has been there a few hundred years. The architecture and dramatic soaring ceilings and stained glass work are truly works of art and is a must see.

It was built around 1960 and is stunning. It is a must visit place. Please remember this is an active place of worship so there are times when only parts can be seen. There is a  video that has a disjoint but interesting history of how. And why it was built.
This is a beautiful Catholic cathedral with masses in both English and Irish. It is located in the middle of Galway and near a bridge which allows for great pictures.
Cool stop, but nothing very special. Used to be an old building, now there's a new one.
Very interesting seeing some of the medieval ruins!
It's cool.
Not an overly exciting location, but interesting information and pretty cool to see history preserved the way it is.
This is a cool stop, and a very neat way to preserve something like this.
It's an arch you walk through. There's nothing wrong with it, it's just not a place you stay at for awhile. The walk around the surrounding town was great though.

The Spanish arch is more of a place to hang out than a historical piece of Galway to visit. During the summer when the weather is good you'll see everyone under the age of 25 there drinking sneaky cans of what ever was cheapest in the off license.
Wonder why this place is counted as attraction. Strolling around in this area is quite nice tho
Interesting! Very easy to find, also very easy to miss if you're not looking for it! Amazing that it's still standing!
As far as I could see it’s an arch will check it out again tomorrow, if anything changes as there must be a interesting story behind it
What an impressive location. Hard by a charming little city. Charming staff.
Beautiful and Lively campus...I enjoy every moment studying here!
Absolutely amazing University, with highly experienced and passionate lecturers.. Campus is beyond beautiful
Great university with beautiful campus
Very nice full
Very nice place for Valentine's day. Booking is essential. Food very high quality. Staff are friendly
Great service, amazing food. Would highly recommend. Hannah and her team are fab 😁

A fine standard of Food, well prepped, not to be faulted. Bit the toilets, which I appreciate are attached to the bar, could only be described as Manky. Disgusting, uncleaned, and worn surfaces. Cost you 2 stars. Otherwise a fine restaurant.
Nice restaurant. Gluten free options available. I went with the steak.
Very good food and staff

I cannot describe this wine bar with my limited vocabulary. A visit to Sheridans is a Galway wine and food experience not to be missed. Go there and see for yourself. You will return again and again. The only problem I've had with this gem of a place is leaving it.

I have been going to the chessmonger at Sheridan’s for over 10 years now. The produce is excellent and the staff have been very good in the past. However my recent experience on two occasions at the store have not been good. There have been long queues of people waiting to be served with only one member of staff available during busy times on a Saturday morning. This morning for example a queue of customers were left waiting while one member of staff was already busy serving and the other left the store to ask staff from upstairs to come down to help in the shop but they refused and so the queue grew!! The staff member was very disgruntled and did not have a pleasant manner at all and didn’t apologize to those she was serving about the delay, instead we were greeted with a very sullen face. Please sort out the staff issues as loyal customers deserve better

We stumbled upon Sheridans while walking around the city and wanted to buy cheese for lunch but then we found out there was a wine bar upstairs.

 It was AMAZING! The cheese and charcuterie were fantastic. The wine was paired perfectly by an incredible sommelier, Michelangelo. He was friendly, knowledgeable and the experience would not have been the same if he were not there. 

A huge thank you to Michelangelo for the wonderful service and chat!! This wine bar is a must if visiting Galway. Cheers!!
v good place to eat
Incredible cheeseeees!!!! And lovely service. Highly recommended : )

Outstanding food and service. If you're looking for good food this is definitely the place to come. We had a variety of dishes: pork, chicken and fish and they were all beautifully cooked. As a started I'd definitely recommend the provolone chicken! Amazing experience!!!!!
I had a lovely meal here. It's best to make a reservation as they can be quite busy. Food was served very quick after ordering and the perfect temp.  I will definitely be having dinner here again.

Seventeen of us arrived at 4pm on Saturday asking to be fed. Very accommodating. Food superb and even let us watch Grand National in private area before reserving us a large table so we could drink together. We spent €1,200 so win win.

Very good food, nice place with lovely staff. It has a massive amount of space and was lovely food, we were there for lunch today while the match was on and didn't get neglected by staff at all. The food was amazingly presented with great proper salads not a small little one that didn't have any thought
Bar is small. Restaurant  large but nicely partitioned.  A little bit dark.Needs to brighten up in interior decoration.  Food almost always good.

Great burritos from friendly staff in this small place with seating upstairs but you're going to need a big appetite to finish one of these meals.

All the usual Mexican style options are here including quesadillas and burritos, with vegetarian options.

Colourful and quirky decor and layout but a great feed.
Rude attendance, horrible songs..
Best place for Turkish food in Galway. My personal favorite. Always fresh and tasty food. Table service just like a restaurant. Nice and clean place. High chair for kids, baby change and toilets.

I have been to Capital Several times. I can say you get best kababs here . The staff is very friendly and prices are reasonable. I had chicken and Mixed doner kebab meals. The taste wise and quantity wise it's amazing.
Best place for halal Turkish food in Galway. Great service and clean nice place.
Very lovely restaurant , perfect food and big portion !
I love the chips. Fresher compared to other fast food restaurants
